{
  "texts": [
    "Benitez et al. (2020) used social exchange theory to develop a six-dimensional framework for investigating the complexities of Industry 4.0 and the roles played by various actors in providing SMEs with digital transformation solutions.",
    "The research used a case study approach to analyze the function of ecosystem members during the startup, growth, and leadership phases.",
    "The adoption paths tend to form clusters based on keywords such as industrialization, complete process, and technology.",
    "The adoption strategies of small and medium-sized businesses (SMEs) in their digital transformation is a topic of ongoing study.",
    "With the help of the Technology-Organization-Environment (TOE) model, Fosso Wamba et al. (2016) analyzed the adoption of RFID systems by SMEs in four countries (India, Australia, the USA, and the UK)."
  ]
}